-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri May 30, 2014 06:06AM EDT
-- None



May 30 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Friday:

** Former Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O> CEO Steve Ballmer has purchased the NBA's Los Angeles Clippers franchise for $2 billion, a record for a professional basketball team, sole trustee Shelly Sterling announced. [ID:nL1N0OG0BB]  ** The retail arm of Hong Kong billionaire Li Ka-shing's Hutchison Whampoa Ltd <0013.HK> said it has agreed to sell its 50 percent interest in a travel services business to joint-venture partner Nuance Group AG for an undisclosed sum. [ID:nL3N0OG08P]  ** French power group GDF Suez <GSZ.PA> said its energy services unit Cofely bought U.S. firm Ecova for $335 million in a bid to expand its energy efficiency business. [ID:nWEB00NVS]